<table width="auto"  border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr><td colspan=3>House Bill/Resolution NO. <b>HB00561</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>FULL TITLE : AN ACT RIGHTSIZING THE NATIONAL GOVERNMENT TO IMPROVE PUBLIC SERVICE DELIVERY</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>ABSTRACT : "Rightsizing the National Government Act"

Seeks to authorize the President to rightsized the executive branch of the government in order to promote a more streamlined and efficient system of operations; and also grants the heads of the Legislature, the Judiciary, Constitutional Offices, LGUS, and SUCs the same authority within their authorized appropriations.

Proposes the creation of the Committee on Rightsizing the National Government which shall oversee
the implementation of this rationalization program aimed at streamlining national government agency
operations thereby promoting a more efficient system of delivery of services.

Intends to ensure a more sustainable pattern of public expenditure through a leaner yet more responsive and effective bureaucracy.
</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>PRINCIPAL AUTHOR/S : <b>ABELLANOSA, RODRIGO A.</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>DATE FILED : 2019-07-01</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SIGNIFICANCE: NATIONAL</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>CO-AUTHORS (Journal Entries) :</td></tr><tr><td>1. Singson-Meehan (000 2019-08-05)</td><td>2. Yap (V.) (000 2019-09-12)</td><tr><td>3. Lopez (M.L.) (000 2019-09-23)</td><tr><td colspan=3><b>ACTIONS TAKEN BY THE COMMITTEE</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>COMMITEE HEARINGS/ACTIONS:</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3><b>&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp1. Referred to Stakeholders on 2019-09-11</b><tr><td colspan=3>&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp-Referred to the Department of Budget and Management for position paper.</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3><b>ACTIONS TAKEN BY THE COMMITTEE ON RULES</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>REFERRAL TO THE COMMITTEE ON GOVERNMENT REORGANIZATION ON 2019-07-23</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SECONDARILY REFERRED TO THE COMMITTEE(S) ON APPROPRIATIONS</td></tr></table>